						               													<description>Meeple Detective is a deduction game that players must compete with other players to trace and apprehend Phantom and his minions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game have 2 PHASES :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;ACTION PHASE&amp;#10;1. Each player must flip 1 card face up permanently and peek adjacent 1 card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2.Check what type of card the player has last faced up.&amp;#10;2.1 If a face up card is a hostage room card or the clue room card : Nothing happened then next player will continue to play.&amp;#10;2.2 If a face up card is an event room card, active player must draw 1 time card and check what type of card opened is: &amp;#10;&amp;gt; investigate : Enter the investigative phase.&amp;#10;&amp;gt; empty room : Nothing happened then next player will continue to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;INVESTIGATION PHASE&amp;#10;1. Starting from active player. Each player may place their Meeple (s) on any room card or pass.&amp;#10;2. If you are a first player of that card, place 1 Meeple, if not, place 2 Meeples.&amp;#10;3. When it comes back to active player, INVESTIGATION PHASE end.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game end immediately after complete investigation phase 4 times. Then, scoring begins. Player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
